This paper discusses the use of entropy-based methods to measure structural diversity in an ensemble of classifiers. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of genetic algorithms to find the optimal ensemble suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of the uncertainty rule from information theory suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the use of ensembles and decision aggregation suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
